sql:
SELECT incident_id, iso_code
FROM incident_iso
WHERE iso_id IS NOT NULL AND iso_code IS NOT NULL;

SELECT incident_id, fatalities
FROM incidents
WHERE year = 2016;

SELECT iso_code, COUNT(*) AS incident_count
FROM incident_iso
GROUP BY iso_code;

external_knowledge:
- "Death toll" refers to the total number of fatalities;
- "Unfortunate events" refers to the incidents;
- "Yearly" means the data is grouped by year.

